         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24/8/77 ¶  ¶ Let me thank you for your interesting photograms, dear Mr Wragge. It requires to know that both cards belong to you. It is kind of you to offer to dry plants for me, should you ever visit...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">77.08.24</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Clement Wragge</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MS 11124, La Trobe Australian Manuscripts Collection, State Library of Victoria, Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24/8/77</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me thank you for your interesting photograms, dear Mr Wragge. It requires to know that both cards belong to you. It is kind of you to offer to dry plants for me, should you ever visit a locality in the backregions of India, known <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg> to have been visited by botanists or collectors,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Presumably Wragge, who was in SA at this time, had indicated to M that he was thinking of going to India.</p>
               </note> then pick up <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">any</hi>
               </seg> plant, and send the parcels <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">by post</hi>
               </seg>, the specimens closely packed and reduced to small flowering &amp; fruiting branches, as advised in the enclosed circular.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B76.04.02.</p>
               </note> Your honored name would of course be quoted along with the plants, in publications emanating therefrom.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Best compl. to Mr Ingleby</p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
